lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO, June 26 — Oracle’s quarterly revenues beat Wall Street’s projections Tuesday as the software company claimed substantial gains over its rivals, SAP and I.B.M.

abstract: The software company continued to ride its three-year buying spree, leading its executives to claim substantial gains over its competitors.
snippet: The software company continued to ride its three-year buying spree, leading its executives to claim substantial gains over its competitors.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO, June 26 — Fourth-quarter revenue at the Oracle Corporation, the software company, beat Wall Street’s projections on Tuesday as it continued to ride its three-year buying spree, leading its executives to claim substantial gains over its competitors.

headline.main: Oracle’s Revenue Climbs 20%, Helped by Acquisitions
headline.print_headline: Oracle’s Revenue Climbs 20%, Helped by Acquisitions
